Daley, the Lake Calumet site was eventually abandoned due to claims that it would be significantly more expensive to build than an alternate, rural site in Peotone, Illinois.","resource_full_text":"","resource_types_for_resource_id":"Archival Material","resource_asset_type":"10","resource_image_thumbnail":"..\/images\/Rsrc_TN_002295.jpg","resource_asset_type_label":"","resource_file_size":"0.0 kB","resource_file_size_unformatted":"43.6474609375","resource_grade_level":"","resource_curriculum":"","resource_tour":"","resource_file_time":"00m 00s","resource_file_time_unformatted":"0","resource_source_detail":"\"Architecture for Urbanism: Selections from the Bertrand Goldberg Archive,\" Case 8, Ryerson &amp; Burnham Libraries, November 1, 2011\u2013January 2, 2012<br \/>\n<br \/>\n<a href=&quot;http:\/\/digital-libraries.saic.edu\/u?\/mqc,14851&quot;>Link to R&amp;B Archives Digital Collections record<\/a>","resource_tags_for_resource_id":"city planning"},"resource_2296":{"resource_link":"..\/2296","resource_url":"http:\/\/www.artic.edu\/aic\/collections\/citi\/resources\/Rsrc_002296.jpg","resource_title":"07. Bertrand Goldberg to Robert C. Wood, Undersecretary Department of Housing and Urban Development (HUD), May 7, 1968.","resource_description":"","resource_full_text":"","resource_types_for_resource_id":"Archival Material","resource_asset_type":"10","resource_image_thumbnail":"..\/images\/Rsrc_TN_002296.jpg","resource_asset_type_label":"","resource_file_size":"0.0 kB","resource_file_size_unformatted":"71.4501953125","resource_grade_level":"","resource_curriculum":"","resource_tour":"","resource_file_time":"00m 00s","resource_file_time_unformatted":"0","resource_source_detail":"\"Architecture for Urbanism: Selections from the Bertrand Goldberg Archive,\" Case 8, Ryerson &amp; Burnham Libraries, November 1, 2011\u2013January 2, 2012<br \/>\n<br \/>\n<a href=&quot;http:\/\/digital-libraries.saic.edu\/u?\/mqc,14902&quot;>Link to R&amp;B Archives Digital Collections recor